{
  "stem": "268.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Where in Czeladz, for instance, which was Poland proper, I remember going to the pump and pumping water.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had indoor water and indoor plumbing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not a private bathroom, but in a hallway.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] Each two apartments had one bathroom.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So as far as the standards in those days, which were probably higher standards, the apartments-- the tenement houses were, probably, I want to guess, I'd say four stories high for about 16 tenements in a house, in a building.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Comfortable buildings, comfortable rooms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Not a whole lot of rooms.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had [INAUDIBLE] a foyer, a big kitchen, and a big living room, which-- actually, a big bedroom, actually, because the kitchen served as a place to eat.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a huge-- huge apartment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we shared.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't have my own room.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We shared.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That would have been considered luxury in those days in Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very, very, very well, except he read a lot at night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He kept me up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was reading, too, but I would read sport pages, and he would read more serious stuff.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a wonderful relationship as far as brothers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's the kind of relationship, I think-- almost if I would cut myself, he would bleed, or vice versa.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was very close.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My favorite part of the house was the part where in the living room, in the particular side of the living room, we had a big radio.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My uncle who lived with us two or three years before the war, he was a salesman.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was selling electronics.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a radio in those days was-- was the-- was almost like digital, or I don't know what the most modern TV is today, but-- but it was-- a radio was-- not everyone had a radio.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
